libxml: constify the storage of xmlGetLastError()

libxml2 recently made it a const return.
Since nothing is being modified of it, this should have no real effect
past satisfying the compiler.

commit.message:
libxml: include parser.h

libxml2 removed the inclusion of global.h in a few of its include files,
so we can no longer rely on transitive includes.

This applies to functions like xmlParseFile.

Signed-off-by: Christopher Degawa <ccom@randomderp.com>

Feel free to reject this PR if you want to keep a separate one for some reason, rather than this being a historical artifact :)

Running 'make docs' with doxygen 1.8.7 gives:
"Warning: No output formats selected! Set at least one of the main
GENERATE_* options to YES."
and even though make is successful, no documentation is generated.
Adding GENERATE_HTML = yes to Doxyfile avoids this.
